sec.p:
Following the finalization of included studies, a standardized data extraction form was developed based on the CHARMS checklist [16]. Two investigators independently performed data extraction, with each model extracted separately when a single study presented multiple models. The extracted information was categorized into two domains:
Basic Information: author, publication year, country, research design, data source, participants, and blood transfusion rate;
Model Information: the number of models developed, quantity of candidate variables, variable selection method, method for processing continuous variables, handling of missing data, model development method, model validation method, model performance measures, calibration methods, final predictors incorporated in the model, and the model presentation format.
